@prabhjyotsingh corrected the test cases. :)

@jongyoul your conclusion are correct. I would also say there is something happeing with the zeppelin.R.render.options`nowt taken into account (the`echo = FALSE` is there to ensure the commands you type are not printed in the result).

Here, it seems the R result is returned with the given command.
Maybe the interperter settings overrides the values defined in the interepreter code?
